    <fr:title text="Horn clause wp for while loops">Horn clause wp for while loops</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Quiz</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  Consider the following while loop:
</html:p><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  W \triangleq  \texttt {while}\ x < n\ \texttt {do}\ x := x + 1
]]></fr:tex><html:p>
  say we wanted to prove the Hoare triple:
</html:p><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \vdash  \{x \leq  n\}\ W\ \{x = n\}
]]></fr:tex><html:p>
  Answer the following questions:  
</html:p><html:ol><html:li>What is <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\texttt {wp}(W, p(x, n))]]></fr:tex></html:li>
  <html:li>Which clauses do we have to add to prove the triple?</html:li>
  <html:li>Do the Horn-clauses match our syntax restrictions?</html:li></html:ol>
  
    
    
